text:
BREAKING: Tory WIN as Trudy Harrison SNATCHES Labour stronghold in Copeland by-election BREAKING: Tory WIN as Trudy Harrison SNATCHES Labour stronghold in Copeland by-election THE Tories have dealt a hammer blow to Jeremy Corbyn’s Labour as Trudy Harrison won over hearts in Copeland in a landmark by-election victory. PUBLISHED: 02:54, Fri, Feb 24, 2017 | UPDATED: 02:56, Fri, Feb 24, 2017 GETTY Conservative Copeland Victory for Trudy Harrison & Theresa May 
Now the first governing party to win a by-election since 1982, the Conservatives were expected to win after Jeremy Corbyn almost admitted defeat to his colleagues hours before the result, branding the by-elections “close and challenging”. 
The turnout at Copeland's by-election was unexpectedly high at 51.35 percent and dispelled fears Storm Doris may put off voters. 
More to follow...
